          instruction: "FOR THE BEEF AND POTATOES: Pat roast dry with paper towels. Combine 21/4 teaspoons salt, 1 teaspoon pepper, and baking soda in small bowl. Rub salt mixture evenly over roast and let stand for 1 hour. After 1 hour, tie roast with kitchen twine at 11/2 inch intervals. Adjust oven rack to middle position and heat oven to 425 degrees."
